						<summary>

						<p>On the south wall, central shrine, Āpatasahāyēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Year 16: 987 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This inscription records that Sembiyaṉ Mādēviyār, the mother of Uttamachōḷa who had caused the construction in stone of the temple of Āḻvār in Tirukkuraṅgāḍutuṟai in Tiraimūr-nāḍu noticed the old inscriptions of this temple engraved earlier were getting erased, had them re-engraved on stone in the 16th regnal year of Uttamachōḷa.</p>						

						<p>Published in <hi rend="italic">S.I.I.,</hi> Vol. III No. 144.</p>						

						</summary>
